<font color="#FF0000">OUR OWN MEMORIAL..</font><br>
<tt>Wed Dec 10 17:14:29 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Paul,<br><br>
  Number on the Pot.. Maybe not everyone did it but an example is on 3MAR68 Co B was ambushed as we ascended hill 881 in the Ashau Valley, that day six men were killed in that ambush. Thus the number 881 was written on the helmet of those who were there... We just needed some way of keeping track of our losses.. it seemed the only way we could keep our own memorial to those who fell in combat. But as we wrote 881 on the helmet.. it was written in our hearts &amp; minds at the same time.. and forever.<br><br>
You just had to be there to understand… been said a thousand times but really is true, to understand just one isolated event you had to have been there for the events leading up to it to understand. And as always different people different views even among those who where there. I agree.. the close to the edge, the closer one is to your on mortality every aspect of life in magnified , higher highs, lower lows..   <br><br>
Reg adding to site.. I hope I can add something worth while..<br><br>
Gary 'J.’<br>

